     <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>A patient weighs 60 kg and is 155 cm tall, if the recommended dose of Doxorubicin is 60 mg/m<sup>2</sup>, what is the patientâ€™s dose?</p>
     <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Estimate the BSA using the Mosteller equation.</p>
     <div class="formulae"> <p> $$ BSA \ m^2 = \sqrt{155 \times 60 \over 3600} = 1.6 \ m^2 $$</p></div>
     <div class="formulae"><p>$$ Patient's Dose = {60 \ mg/m^2 \times 1.6 \ m^2 } = 96 \ mg $$</p></div>
     <p><span style="color:black"><strong>Answer: </strong></span> 96 mg</p>
     
